[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi folks,<br>\nI asked this question on Twitter, let me echo it here: <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mattecapu/status/1562816006204321793?s=20&amp;t=HAdCYkJQzKBCT_ukhej4ag\">https://twitter.com/mattecapu/status/1562816006204321793?s=20&amp;t=HAdCYkJQzKBCT_ukhej4ag</a></p>\n<div class=\"inline-preview-twitter\"><div class=\"twitter-tweet\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/mattecapu/status/1562816006204321793?s=20&amp;t=HAdCYkJQzKBCT_ukhej4ag\"><img class=\"twitter-avatar\" src=\"https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/6aa2f4e0661ba68daabb4fcbf5b432996abf0eb7/68747470733a2f2f7062732e7477696d672e636f6d2f70726f66696c655f696d616765732f313530363539393233313731323338323937372f2d777954346b46715f6e6f726d616c2e6a7067\"></a><p>can anyone motivate why lifting properties are stated for squares instead of cospans? i.e. why i and f are there in this def? <a href=\"https://t.co/81VoOaTC1w\">https://twitter.com/mattecapu/status/1562816006204321793/photo/1</a></p><span>- Matteo Capucci (@mattecapu)</span><div class=\"twitter-image\"><a href=\"https://t.co/81VoOaTC1w\"><img src=\"https://uploads.zulipusercontent.net/538f52c35c70222416addc107bcef56f1360c075/68747470733a2f2f7062732e7477696d672e636f6d2f6d656469612f46624138596250575141414e5541722e706e673a6c61726765\"></a></div></div></div>",
        "id": 295250551,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661439996
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>To clarify, I'm asking why lifting properties are not stated as 'for every <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">g</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span> of (some nice class of morphisms) there is a lift <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">q</span></span></span></span> such that (bunch of properties)'</p>",
        "id": 295250859,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661440091
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/0gTdHFUMuHLFS-755C8ZRVsN/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/0gTdHFUMuHLFS-755C8ZRVsN/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/21317/0gTdHFUMuHLFS-755C8ZRVsN/image.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 295251062,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661440155
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd like to know that as well! The only \"motivation\" I know of is that it subsumes lifting and extension properties.</p>",
        "id": 295252993,
        "sender_full_name": "Tobias Schmude",
        "timestamp": 1661440725
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This was already basically answered on Twitter, but the simplest example from topology would be that we have a map <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p : X \\to Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span>, and we want to lift a path <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>γ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\gamma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05556em;\">γ</span></span></span></span> in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span> to a path in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span> that starts at a specified lift of the initial point of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>γ</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\gamma</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05556em;\">γ</span></span></span></span>. Diagrammatically, that is a condition involving a square with <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mn>0</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo><mo>→</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">[</mo><mn>0</mn><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mn>1</mn><mo stretchy=\"false\">]</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{0\\} \\to [0, 1]</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">[</span><span class=\"mord\">0</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mclose\">]</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p : X \\to Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span> as its two sides.</p>",
        "id": 295253082,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1661440760
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note that the condition is about <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>i</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6595em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">i</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span>, and quantifies over all <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">g</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span></span></span></span>. If <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">A</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span></span></span></span> is the initial object, so that the diagram reduces to the one you drew, it would still be a condition about <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span> that quantifies over all <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">g</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span></span></span></span>, not a condition about all <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>g</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">g</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">g</span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 295256282,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1661441748
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>On the other hand, lifting in a square is the same as lifting in a cospan in a coslice category...</p>",
        "id": 295291567,
        "sender_full_name": "Mike Shulman",
        "timestamp": 1661453762
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Might be worth observing that with different quantification on the cospan you can instead define <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/projective%20object\">[[projective object]]</a> s.</p>",
        "id": 295302805,
        "sender_full_name": "Morgan Rogers (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661458074
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh, I completely misunderstood your question on Twitter, Matteo.     I thought you were wanting to do something really weird.</p>",
        "id": 295309462,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1661461049
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In fact, the kind of lifting property you're talking about is very commonly used and important.   For example it shows up in the definition of <a href=\"https://ncatlab.org/nlab/show/projective%20module\">[[projective module]]</a>.</p>",
        "id": 295309647,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1661461121
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>However as Barton pointed out, in topology (and elsewhere) we <em>also</em> often want to look at a combination of lifting and extension.  His example is the fundamental one: we are trying to lift a path in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span> to a path in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span>, but we have already chosen how to lift the starting point of that path, so we are extending that lift to a lift of the whole path.</p>",
        "id": 295310055,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1661461297
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This example should remind you of the concept of Grothendieck (op)fibration.</p>",
        "id": 295310173,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1661461331
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks everyone for the replies :) I now see the point behind a square, as a lift with an extension condition (or an extension with a lifting condition)</p>",
        "id": 295370049,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661499877
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yesterday I was playing with actions and spans and I wondered what the action of a monad in span(C) on another endomorphism looks like<br>\nMonads in span(C) are categories, so this almost recovers actions of categories, but there's an extra condition. Indeed what you get is the 'action of a category on a graph', i.e. you get a composition operation that takes an arrow of a graph (internal to C) and extends it with an arrow of the acting category: <a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/CoExEuG2uNnJHbC7hk8_ZEjo/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/CoExEuG2uNnJHbC7hk8_ZEjo/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/21317/CoExEuG2uNnJHbC7hk8_ZEjo/image.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 295370459,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661500097
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(It is crucial that both the graph and the category share the same set of vertices/objects)</p>",
        "id": 295370508,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661500122
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Call the acting category <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\">M</span></span></span></span></span>. The thing above is an action of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\">M</span></span></span></span></span> on a graph <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>C</mi><mo>←</mo><mi>E</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G : C \\leftarrow E \\to C</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">←</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">E</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 295370614,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661500180
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If we swap the legs of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">M</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal M</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\">M</span></span></span></span></span> we get <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"script\">M</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">p</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal M^{op}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\">M</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>. Now a (right) action of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"script\">M</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">p</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal M^{op}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\">M</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> on <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span> is an operation such as</p>",
        "id": 295370766,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661500235
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/ZS0UJfTQKG6WlAZesNnr4rnQ/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/ZS0UJfTQKG6WlAZesNnr4rnQ/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/21317/ZS0UJfTQKG6WlAZesNnr4rnQ/image.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 295370798,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661500253
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>and we can read <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>∙</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f \\bullet m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∙</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span> as 'the lift of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span> along <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">m</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span></span></span></span>'</p>",
        "id": 295370856,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661500285
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The laws of action tell us that <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>∙</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>m</mi><mo separator=\"true\">;</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>∙</mo><mi>m</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo separator=\"true\">;</mo><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f \\bullet (m ; n) = (f \\bullet m) ; n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∙</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span><span class=\"mpunct\">;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∙</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">m</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mpunct\">;</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo>∙</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f \\bullet 1 = f</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∙</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span></span></span></span>, which seem reasonable conditions for a lifting operation</p>",
        "id": 295370941,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661500322
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Dually, a left action of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant=\"script\">M</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"script\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"script\">p</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\cal M^{op}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathcal\">M</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">o</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> gives an extension operation:</p>",
        "id": 295371033,
        "sender_full_name": "Matteo Capucci (he/him)",
        "timestamp": 1661500360
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/HwYQxmOBSNEW9YMUBFWgcByN/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/21317/HwYQxmOBSNEW9YMUBFWgcByN/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/21317/HwYQxmOBSNEW9YMUBFWgcByN/image.png\"></a></div>",
        "id": 295371035,
